\title{Limit Point}
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{boat}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{math-lib}

\p{
Let #{(X, \tau)} be a [topological space](gtop-0002) and #{S \subseteq X}. A point #{x \in X} is a \strong{limit point} of #{S} if every [open set](gtop-0005) containing #{x} also contains a point of #{S} other than #{x} itself.
}

\p{
In a [metric space](gtop-0003), this is equivalent to: there exists a sequence #{\set{x_n} \subseteq S \setminus \set{x}} such that #{x_n \to x}.
}
